snippet: Distributors are reviewing low-rated channels, and those without a major media company to back them are in danger of being dropped.
abstract: Major media companies and distributors are reviewing profitability of low-rated cable channels, raising possibility that many of them could be dropped; shift is related to new competition from Web providers as well as soaring programing costs.
lead_paragraph: Distributors are reviewing low-rated channels, and those without a major media company to back them are in danger of being dropped.

headline.seo: Cable Channels Like Current and Ovation Feeling Heat
headline.main: Cable Companies Squeeze More Obscure Channels
headline.print_headline: Cable Companies Squeeze More Obscure Channels
